In .NET MAUI, use the **lifecycle events** API in your `MauiProgram.cs` (or anywhere you configure the app builder):

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity =>
        {
            // Runs when Android activity is paused
        })
        .OnStop(activity =>
        {
            // Runs when Android activity is stopped
        }));
#endif

#if IOS
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app =>
        {
            // Runs when iOS app enters background
        }));
#endif
});
```

**Key points:**

- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` at the top.
- Platform directives (`#if ANDROID`, `#if IOS`) ensure each block only compiles for the target platform.
- The builder methods (`AddAndroid`, `AddiOS`) expose the full native lifecycle — you can chain additional events like `.OnResume()`, `.WillTerminate()`, etc.
- For cross-platform background detection without platform code, you can also subscribe to `Window.Deactivated` or `App.OnSleep()`, though these are less granular.
